SIMPLE: management
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Management
<hw>Man"age*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Manage</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or art of
managing; the manner of treating, directing, carrying on, or using, for
a purpose; conduct; administration; guidance; control; <as>as, the
<ex>management</ex> of a family or of a farm; the <ex>management</ex> of
a business enterprise; the <ex>management</ex> of state
affairs.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>management</xex> of the
voice.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>E. Porter.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Business dealing; negotiation;
arrangement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had great <qex>managements</qex> with ecclesiastics.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Judicious use of means to accomplish an end; conduct
directed by art or address; skillful treatment; cunning practice; --
often in a bad sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mark with what <qex>management</qex> their tribes divide⟦br⟧
Some stick to you, and some to t'other side.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The collective body of those who manage or direct
any enterprise or interest; the board of managers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Conduct; administration; government; direction;
guidance; care; charge; contrivance; intrigue.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>management consultant</ent>⟦br⟧
